text: William Francis Raborn, Jr., (June 8, 1905 - March 6, 1990) was the United States Director of Central Intelligence from April 28, 1965 until June 30, 1966. He was also a career United States Navy officer who lead the project to develop the Polaris missile system and retired from the Navy in 1963 as a Vice Admiral. ==References== Category:1905 births Category:1990 deaths Category:American military personnel of World War II Category:Directors of the Central Intelligence Agency Category:Military people from Texas
